The isotopic composition of the basic material

Cf-252 sample as spot of californium oxide of 15 mm
diameter, deposited on a 25 microm thick Al foil.
The activity at moment of preparation (November 2002)
37 kBq, corresponding to 0.0019 microg of Cf-252.

The energy calibration was done based on radioactive

-Measurement with two different telescope detectors was
performed to examine the spontaneous fission of Cf-252.
Telescope 1 -for the detection of ternary LRA and He-6,
telescope 2 -to detect tritons. Since the Cf-252 sample
has an Al backing, both telescopes could be
simultaneously mounted in a vacuum chamber. For ternary
fission measurements, the deltaE detector facing the
sample was shielded with a 25 microm thick Al foil.
Separate measurement with a third telescope was
performed to examine the non-Gaussian tailing on the
